This program uses a switch statement to determine a color associated with a number 1-4. If the isn't with in 1-4 the number is displayed as invalid.

**/
import java.util.Scanner;

class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.println("Number?");
    int userNumber = input.nextInt();
    System.out.println("");
    switch (userNumber - 1) {

      case 0: System.out.println("1 is Cyan."); break;

      case 1: System.out.println("2 is Magenta."); break;

      case 2: System.out.println("3 is Yellow."); break;

      case 3: System.out.println("4 is Black."); break;

      default: System.out.println("That number is not valid."); break;

    }
  }
}
